This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:43 AM Defendant Victoria Ann Marie Linderman in court.  Attorney Fredric B. Anderson in court for Victoria Ann Marie Linderman.  Attorney Chad C La Lor in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. State calls witness. Witness sworn and testified. Jerod Steven Rankila, Police Officer, SPD. August 3, 2022. City of Superior, Douglas County, WI. Witness identifies Defendant. Court reflects identification of defendant. Attorney cross examines witness. State redirects. State rests. 
State makes argument for bind over. Attorney makes argument in opposition. Court finds probable cause and binds the Defendant over for Arraignment. 
Court reminds the Defendant of their bail conditions. Defendant orally confirms they have received date and time of hearing and confirms they will attend. Defendant provided notice.
Arraignment scheduled for October 21, 2022 at 09:30 am.
No use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription.

1:29 PM Defendant Victoria Ann Marie Linderman appeared by video, in custody. Attorney Ryan Reid appears with Defendant.  Attorney Peter Kruger in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Address verified. Attorney acknowledges complaint, waives reading, requests preliminary hearing, pleads not guilty to Count 2. Court accepts plea.
State requests $1000 cash, no use or possession of drugs or paraphernalia. No ties to douglas County.
Attorney Reid asks for signature bond. St. Paul ties. In the alternative, $100 cash.
Court orders $1000 cash, conditions of no use or possession of drugs or drug paraphernalia
Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 10, 2022 at 10:45 am.
